                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17991030-34-off193 t17991030-34-victim347"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17991030-34-person348">
                  JOSEPH
                   WARD
               <interp inst="t17991030-34-person348" type="surname" value="WARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17991030-34-person348" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17991030-34-person348" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - On the 18th of September, I found Mr. Bellis's waggon tilt-cloth, in the prisoner's bag; it was missed between the 17th and 18th; I found it in a wood, in the parish of Pinner, about two miles from Mr. Bellis's; I sent for Mr. Bellis, and he owned it; the prisoner owned that it was his sack, I asked him what he had got in it, he was lying down by the sack; he said he had got nothing of mine; I insisted upon knowing what he had got in the sack; he pulled out a kettle with ribs of lamb in it, and about a yard of cloth, with the man's name upon it, one whole breadth; the other part was lying by him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17991030-34-person349">
                  JOHN
                   KING
               <interp inst="t17991030-34-person349" type="surname" value="KING"></interp>
